…is the title of my presentation about building serverless applications using OpenWhisk.
Abstract Servers are killing your productivity. Rather than building better software for your users, you end up constantly distracted by maintaining computers. Wasn&rsquo;t the &ldquo;cloud&rdquo; supposed to fix this? It sounded so promising until we realised it was just renting VMs in someone else&rsquo;s datacenter. We couldn&rsquo;t escape &ldquo;servers&rdquo;. Until now&hellip;
In this session, developers will learn how to build microservices without servers, using modern “serverless” cloud platforms.
